# BetOnMe Vite dev server config
#
# Copy this file to BetOnMe/.env.local (which is gitignored) and edit
# values to match your workflow.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET — where to send /api/* calls from the dev server
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Default (unset): http://localhost:3000
#   Use this when you're running the Next.js backend yourself with
#   `npm run dev` from the repo root. Best for backend work.
#
# Set to the deployed Vercel URL when you want to do frontend-only work
# (visual polish, copy changes, layout tweaks) without spinning up
# Mongo / XRPL / Gemini locally. Login, goals, proofs all just work
# against the live backend.
#
#   VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=https://hackku2026.vercel.app
#
# After editing this file, restart `npm run dev` for the change to
# take effect.
